Launches a billed agent session over a target project directory, executing either a headless task (with a brief) or an interactive Claude TUI, authenticated via the operator's Claude Code subscription. On successful completion, optionally regenerates context summaries via `ctx-scan --update` with hardcoded model choices.

The summary refresh is the only place regeneration occurs; it runs post-session only on success (`exit_code == 0`) and never fails the run itself—the session's deliverable has already landed. The operator must explicitly opt in via a y/N prompt (which only appears in a real terminal; piped/CI runs skip it and print a manual recovery command instead). The refresh inherits agent config from `~/.config/ctx/env` (which must be `0600` when present) but passes only `CTX_AGENT_CMD` and `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` into the child's environment, never into the shell or cage. Model choices are hardcoded: `claude-haiku-4-5-20251001` for leaves, `claude-sonnet-5` for rollups—this is the one automated caller that always wants these, so they are not exposed as flags.

Warns (does not fail) if the target lacks `.claude/settings.json`, since the context-chain hook will not lead the session. Task ID defaults to `run-<pid>`. Dirty-tree checks reject by default unless `--allow-dirty` is set.